<br>
Actually LoH has been screwed up for a long time.  LoH was always intended to be a complete heal when EQ came out.  The problem was that when they released Kunark they f'd everything up having to do with the post-50 game.  VI continually changed their position on what LoH was supposed to be and still do on occasion.  It was a complete heal.  Then, VI felt it was being abused because lvl paladins were CH'ing lvl 60's.  Then VI changes LoH to make it so that it's not a CH but that it will CH someone your own level.  Then, with Velious and Luclin, players are able to get more hit points than LoH can cover.  With Luclin they give us a class ability to make LoH a complete heal again after we get a minimum of 23 aa points.<br>
<br>
Fit more with &quot;fairness&quot; of the spell?  Give me a break.  Making a paladin use 5aa to have an ability do what is is supposed to do is ridiculous.  Beside, Kainzo, (who has the amazing ability to tell pallies to get Improved LOH twice in a two sentence post) you can't get it until you are lvl 59 or 60 and that screws all the pallies under that level.  You shouldn't have to be lvl 59 or 60 to have your abilities work properly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukainzoofbots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kainzo of BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/29/02 1:03:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=180.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Attn: Paladins...   Lay on Hands Stealth NERF... or bug?</span><hr size=1> if it matters that much then work hard for what you want, Paladins have sucked for 3 years :P and just now they are starting to get respectable.. I know its a &quot;bug&quot; now not a 'nerf' so even more reason to not worry about it and just suck it up. <br>
